{"title_page": "2015 in Absolute Championship Berkut", "text_new": "{{short description|Mixed martial arts event}}\n{{unreferenced|date=December 2016}}\n{{Year in Combat Sports\n|name = 2015 in Absolute Championship Berkut\n|image =    \n|image_size =    \n|first_date = January 31, 2015\n|last_date = December 27, 2015\n|total_events = 20\n|mma_events = 16\n|kickboxing_events = 4\n|bjj_events =\n|total_fights =    \n|title_fights = \n|preceded_by = [[2014 in Absolute Championship Berkut|2014 in ACB]]\n|followed_by = [[2016 in Absolute Championship Berkut|2016 in ACB]] \n}}\n\nThe year '''2015''' was the 3rd year in the history of the [[Absolute Championship Berkut]], a [[mixed martial arts]] promotion based in [[Russia]]. 2015 started with Absolute Championship Berkut 13. It started broadcasting through a television agreement with  [[Match TV]].\n\n==ACB Grand Prix 2015 bracket==\n\n===ACB Flyweight Grand Prix 2015 bracket===\n\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=1st Round<br/><small> </small> \n| RD2=Semifinals<br/><small> </small> \n| RD3=Final<br/><small> </small>  \n\n| team-width=150\n| score-width=20\n\n| RD1-team1={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Oskar Dolchin'''\n| RD1-score1=\n| RD1-team2={{flagicon|RUS}} Rasul Albaskhanov<sup>1</sup> \n| RD1-score2=\n\n| RD1-team3={{flagicon|BRA}} Irmeson Oliveira\n| RD1-score3='''3r.'''\n| RD1-team4={{flagicon|UKR}} '''Ruslan Abiltarov''' \n| RD1-score4='''DEC'''\n\n| RD1-team5={{flagicon|FIN}} '''Mikael Silander'''\n| RD1-score5=\n| RD1-team6={{flagicon|RUS}} Yunus Evloev<sup>2</sup> \n| RD1-score6=\n\n| RD1-team7={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Velimurad Alkhasov''' \n| RD1-score7='''SUB'''\n| RD1-team8={{flagicon|RUS}} Alexey Pastorov \n| RD1-score8='''2r.'''\n\n| RD2-team1={{flagicon|RUS}} Oscar Dolchin\n| RD2-score1='''3r.'''\n| RD2-team2={{flagicon|UKR}} '''Ruslan Abiltarov''' \n| RD2-score2='''DEC'''\n\n| RD2-team3={{flagicon|FIN}} Mikael Silander \n| RD2-score3='''3r.'''\n| RD2-team4={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Velimurad Alkhasov'''\n| RD2-score4='''DEC'''\n\n| RD3-team1={{flagicon|UKR}} Ruslan Abiltarov  \n| RD3-score1='''2r.'''\n| RD3-team2={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Velimurad Alkhasov''' \n| RD3-score2='''KO'''\n}}\n\n<sup>1</sup>Rasul Albaskhanov retired from the tournament, Albaskhanov missed weight, and the bout was canceled. Oskar Dolchin automatically advanced to the second round.\n\n<sup>2</sup>Yunus Evloev withdrew from the tournament dud to illness, Mikael Silander automatically advanced to the second round.\n\n===ACB Bantamweight Grand Prix 2015 bracket===\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=1st Round<br/><small> </small> \n| RD2=Semifinals<br/><small> </small> \n| RD3=Final<br/><small> </small>  \n\n| team-width=150\n| score-width=20\n\n| RD1-team1={{flagicon|CZE}} '''Filip Macek'''\n| RD1-score1='''SUB'''\n| RD1-team2={{flagicon|RUS}} Murad Zeinulabidov\n| RD1-score2='''3r.'''\n\n| RD1-team3={{flagicon|UKR}} Alexey Naumov\n| RD1-score3='''1r.'''\n| RD1-team4={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Murad Kalamov'''  \n| RD1-score4='''SUB'''\n\n| RD1-team5={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Kharon Orzumiev'''  \n| RD1-score5='''SUB'''\n| RD1-team6={{flagicon|RUS}} Ilfat Amirov  \n| RD1-score6='''1r.'''\n\n| RD1-team7={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Petr Yan''' \n| RD1-score7='''DEC'''\n| RD1-team8={{flagicon|BRA}} Renato Velame \n| RD1-score8='''3r.'''\n\n| RD2-team1={{flagicon|CZE}} Filip Macek\n| RD2-score1='''2r.'''\n| RD2-team2={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Murad Kalamov''' \n| RD2-score2='''SUB'''\n\n| RD2-team3={{flagicon|RUS}} Kharon Orzumiev\n| RD2-score3='''1r.'''\n| RD2-team4={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Petr Yan'''\n| RD2-score4='''SUB'''\n\n| RD3-team1={{flagicon|RUS}} Murad Kalamov  \n| RD3-score1='''3r.'''\n| RD3-team2={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Petr Yan'''\n| RD3-score2='''DEC'''\n}}\n\n===ACB Featherweight Grand Prix 2015 bracket===\n\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=1st Round<br/><small> </small> \n| RD2=Semifinals<br/><small> </small> \n| RD3=Final<br/><small> </small>  \n\n| team-width=150\n| score-width=20\n\n| RD1-team1={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Alexander Matmuratov'''\n|