oke)\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|3:05\n| \n|-\n|Featherweight 66&nbsp;kg\n|{{flagicon|RUS}} Adlan Bataev\n|def.\n|{{flagicon|RUS}} Oleg Peterimov       \n|Decision (Unanimous)\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5:00\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Absolute Championship Akhmat]]\n[[Category:2015 in mixed martial arts]]\n[[Category:2015 in Russian sport|Absolute Championship Berkut events]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Mixed martial arts event}}\n{{unreferenced|date=December 2016}}\n{{Year in Combat Sports\n|name = 2015 in Absolute Championship Berkut\n|image =    \n|image_size =    \n|first_date = January 31, 2015\n|last_date = December 27, 2015\n|total_events = 20\n|mma_events = 16\n|kickboxing_events = 4\n|bjj_events =\n|total_fights =    \n|title_fights = \n|preceded_by = [[2014 in Absolute Championship Berkut|2014 in ACB]]\n|followed_by = [[2016 in Absolute Championship Berkut|2016 in ACB]] \n}}\n\nThe year '''2015''' was the 3rd year in the history of the [[Absolute Championship Berkut]], a [[mixed martial arts]] promotion based in [[Russia]]. 2015 started with Absolute Championship Berkut 13. It started broadcasting through a television agreement with  [[Match TV]].\n\n==ACB Grand Prix 2015 bracket==\n\n===ACB Flyweight Grand Prix 2015 bracket===\n\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=1st Round<br/><small> </small> \n| RD2=Semifinals<br/><small> </small> \n| RD3=Final<br/><small> </small>  \n\n| team-width=150\n| score-width=20\n\n| RD1-team1={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Oskar Dolchin'''\n| RD1-score1=\n| RD1-team2={{flagicon|RUS}} Rasul Albaskhanov<sup>1</sup> \n| RD1-score2=\n\n| RD1-team3={{flagicon|BRA}} Irmeson Oliveira\n| RD1-score3='''3r.'''\n| RD1-team4={{flagicon|UKR}} '''Ruslan Abiltarov''' \n| RD1-score4='''DEC'''\n\n| RD1-team5={{flagicon|FIN}} '''Mikael Silander'''\n| RD1-score5=\n| RD1-team6={{flagicon|RUS}} Yunus Evloev<sup>2</sup> \n| RD1-score6=\n\n| RD1-team7={{flagicon|RUS}} '''Velimurad Alkhasov''' \n| RD1-score7='''SUB'''